+---
+name: multica-publishing-blog
+description: "Use when the user asks to turn content into a published technical document or blog post — e.g. 'write this up as a technical doc', 'publish this to the blog', 'post this as an article', '把这个写成技术文档/发到博客'. Backed by the `multica blog` CLI talking to the inair_website_blog API (Odoo, auth='openapi'). Publishes Markdown as a DRAFT into the agent-dedicated blog by default; a human reviews and publishes it. Covers publish / list / get / update, the draft-by-default contract, the agent-dedicated blog, zero-config X-GALAXY auth, and how a missing install or missing permission surfaces. Do NOT pass --publish unless the user explicitly asks to publish now. Traced to server/cmd/multica/cmd_blog.go and inair_website_blog/controllers/blog_api.py."
+user-invocable: false
+allowed-tools: Bash(multica *)
+---
+
+# Publishing a technical doc to the blog
+
+This skill is the contract for the `multica blog` CLI, which publishes Markdown
+to the Inair website blog (`inair_website_blog`). Every claim below is pinned to
+source in `references/publishing-blog-source-map.md`.
+
+## The end-to-end flow
+
+1. You write the document as Markdown to a file in the working directory.
+2. `multica blog publish --title "…" --file doc.md` creates a **draft** post.
+3. The command prints the post id, state, and `URL:` on stdout.
+4. You report that URL back to the user (typically in an issue comment) so a
+   human can review and publish it on the website.
+
+A draft is the default and the point: the agent-dedicated blog is a review
+queue. A human edits and publishes; the agent does not publish unless asked.
+
+## The contract (what is true by construction)
+
+- **Draft by default.** `publish` sends `is_published=false`; only `--publish`
+  flips it. (decision 2)
+- **Agent-dedicated blog.** With no `--blog`, the post lands in the seeded
+  「智能体技术文档」blog (or whatever `inair_website_blog.default_blog_id`
+  points at). `--blog <id>` overrides it; `multica blog list` lists ids.
+  (decision 3)
+- **Markdown in, HTML stored.** `publish` sends `content_format: "markdown"`; the
+  server converts via `inair_multica.utils.md_to_html`. Send Markdown, not HTML.
+- **Zero-config auth.** In `MULTICA_BACKEND_MODE=odoo` the shared APIClient sets
+  the `X-GALAXY-ACCESS-TOKEN` / `X-GALAXY-API-KEY` headers the
+  `auth='openapi'` endpoints require. The daemon injects them into the agent
+  process, so no token setup is needed inside an agent run.
+- **Path is not under /api.** `/inair_website_blog/...` is left untouched by the
+  client's prefix rewrite and reaches the Odoo controller directly.
+
+## Commands
+
+```
+multica blog list                                   # list blogs (id, name, posts)
+multica blog publish --title "Title" --file doc.md  # create a draft (stdin if no --file)
+multica blog publish --title "Title" --file doc.md --tag Odoo --tag 文档
+multica blog get 42                                 # show one post
+multica blog update 42 --publish                    # publish a draft
+multica blog update 42 --title "New title" --file doc.md
+```
+
+Flags on `publish`: `--title` (required), `--file` (stdin if omitted),
+`--blog <id>`, `--subtitle`, `--tag` (repeatable), `--publish`, `--output json`.
+Flags on `update`: `--title`, `--subtitle`, `--file`, `--tag` (repeatable, replaces),
+`--publish` (`--publish=false` unpublishes), `--output json`.
+
+Use `--output json` when you need to read a field programmatically; the human
+text form already prints the `URL:` line for the common case.
+
+## What does NOT happen (so the result doesn't surprise you)
+
+- **No auto-publish.** Without `--publish` the post is a draft and is not
+  visible on the website. That is intended.
+- **No blog is created.** `publish` targets an existing blog (the agent blog by
+  default). If there is no blog at all, the API returns `400 no target blog
+  available`.
+- **Tags are names, not ids.** Repeatable `--tag "Name"`; the server matches
+  case-insensitively and creates missing tags.
+- **Auth/permission failures are not retried by the CLI.** They surface as:
+  - `401` / `Access token …` → the run is not in Odoo backend mode, or the
+    daemon did not inject X-GALAXY creds. Not something to fix from inside the
+    run; report it.
+  - `403` / `access denied` → the agent's Odoo user is not in the
+    「智能体博客作者」group (which implies the website designer group that holds
+    blog write ACLs), or the `inair_website_blog` module is not installed.
+    Report it as a setup step for a human admin — do not attempt to grant it.
+
+## Incorrect → Correct
+
+Incorrect: pasting raw HTML as `--file`.
+  → the server treats it as Markdown; tags get escaped. Send Markdown.
+
+Incorrect: `multica blog publish --title "X"` with no file and no piped stdin
+in a non-interactive run.
+  → it blocks reading stdin, or sends empty content. Write the doc to a file
+    first, or pipe it: `cat doc.md | multica blog publish --title "X"`.
+
+Incorrect: assuming the post is live because publish returned a URL.
+  → the URL exists but the post is a draft until a human publishes it
+    (`is_published` in the output says which).
+
+Correct:
+  1. Write the doc to `./tech-note.md`.
+  2. `multica blog publish --title "Odoo 19 website_blog 二次开发" --file ./tech-note.md`
+  3. Read the `URL:` line from stdout.
+  4. Post the URL back to the user, noting it is a draft awaiting review.
+
+## References
+
+`references/publishing-blog-source-map.md` — file:line evidence for the CLI
+flags, the Odoo-mode X-GALAXY auth wiring, the non-/api path passthrough, the
+API endpoints and their request/response shapes, the seeded agent blog, and the
+author permission group.
